message.content:
To get to the grocery store that is 1km away in Senegal, you have a few transportation options:

1. Walking: If the weather is pleasant and you have the time, walking can be a good option. It will take approximately 10-15 minutes to cover a distance of 1km.

2. Bicycling: If you have a bicycle or can rent one, it can be a faster and more convenient way to reach the grocery store. It will take around 5-10 minutes to cover the distance.

3. Public Transportation: Depending on the availability in your area, you can check for local buses or minibusses (known as "car rapides" in Senegal) that may pass by or near the grocery store. Ask locals or check with the nearest bus stop for information on routes and timings.

4. Taxi: Taxis are a common mode of transportation in Senegal. You can easily find a taxi on the road or at designated taxi stands. Negotiate the fare with the driver before starting the journey.

5. Ride-Sharing Services: If available in your area, you can use ride-sharing apps like Uber or Bolt to book a car to take you to the grocery store. These services are convenient and provide estimated fares upfront.

Consider the factors such as cost, convenience, and availability while choosing the mode of transportation that suits you best.
